caption.text:
The Full Strategy 👇

1. Identify 10-15 creators in your niche. Research and find 10-15 of their reels that performed exceptionally well in the past 30 days.

2. Create a list of these reels and start recreating them. Don’t just copy—slightly change the hook, write a better caption, or use different audio.

Some great hooks you can use:

• The reason I stopped _
• Stop blaming _ if you’re still struggling with _
• I just found the best _
• Why _ is the worst advice for _
• Why people aren’t talking about _
• Looking to _? Start with _
• If only more people realized _

3. Keep your videos short, around 7-10 seconds, to maximize retention and watch time.

4. Focus on shareability and saves.

Create content you’d be excited to share with a friend. 

Think of valuable knowledge, motivation, tips, or ideas that your ideal follower would want to save and revisit or share with others.

5. Give it enough time: Stick with this for at least a month to see which content performs best for you.

6. Double down: After analyzing your top performers, adopt a 50/50 strategy next month. Seek new content while remaking the best-performing ones.

Want to know the full strategy that helped me grow over 700K followers in 14 months?

Follow me and comment “Strategy” to get the course for free. 📈

Use these settings to boost your growth ↓

First, let’s ensure you’re posting high-quality content!

1️⃣ High-Quality Reels

Step 1: Go to “Settings and Privacy.”
Step 2: Select “Media quality” under “Your app and media.”
Step 3: Turn on “Upload at highest quality.”

→ High-Quality Reels on Instagram are key for grabbing attention, showing professionalism, and standing out!

2️⃣ Suggested Accounts - Vital!

Step 1: Log in to Instagram on your laptop or phone.
Step 2: Go to your profile and click “Edit profile.”
Step 3: Scroll down and enable “Show account suggestions” on profiles.

→ This boosts your profile’s discoverability when someone follows a similar account.

3️⃣ Train the Algorithm

Step 1: Visit the Explore page or the reels tab on your phone.
Step 2: Like and comment on reels or posts within your niche.
Step 3: When a niche reel appears on your feed, share it with someone.

→ This tells Instagram the type of content you post, increasing your visibility.

🤍 BONUS: Comment “Reels” and I’ll send you a free course on creating viral reels!

🙏 Share this to help someone grow their IG!

caption.text:
700K+ followers in 12 months (Here’s how):

At the beginning of last year, I started taking my personal brand on IG seriously.

Back then, I only had one page, and I decided to post every single day no matter what.

Today, I have over 500K followers on that page, as well as 200K on another.

Here are crucial lessons I’ve learned along this journey:

1. Strategic approach:

Many post daily for months without success because they don’t optimize their content. 

Instagram shows what works; no need to search elsewhere. 

Study successful content types to improve chances with the algorithm. 

It’s better to take your time to do proper research and post less frequently than to post daily with mediocre content.

2. Replicable content:

Produce content that can be replicated. Build on successful videos and generate spinoffs for continuous expansion.

For example, if you’re in the fitness niche and your video “Best ways to grow your legs” went viral, you could create these related videos:

- My leg growth journey using this single exercise
- Common mistakes that hinder leg growth
- Exercises to avoid for leg growth

Keep the momentum going with similar variations.

3. Shareability:

Instagram has officially announced that sends per impression is the highest engagement lever.

If your content can generate a lot of shares, it will be pushed out more and reach a broader audience.

Create content that sparks emotion to encourage shares.

This boosts engagement and helps you reach a wider audience.

Need more help growing your Instagram?

Comment “Help” and I’ll send you a free 10-lesson course to assist you on your journey.
